value.0: Hoar's Dogma: Uphold true and fitting justice and maintain the spirit of the law, not the letter of the law. Fitting recompense will always accrue for one's actions. Violence will meet violence and evil pay back evil, but good will also come to those who do good. Walk the line of the Doombringer's teachings, seeking retribution, but do not fall into the trap of pursuing evil acts for evil's sake, for that way is seductive and leads only to one's downfall. Vengeance must be sought for all injustices, and all punishments must fit the crime. Revenge is sweetest when it is sharpened with irony. All attacks must be avenged. Those who do not respond to attacks against their person or that which they hold dear only invite future attacks.

3, Year of the Faded Flower: Rise of Aleaxtis in Sers. The Sahuagin emerge from a century of war with the merrow of the Alamber to claim more than half of the sea as their own.
907, Year of Waiting: Prince Ankh'Remun establishes a Mulhorandi colony on the island Khem.
922, Year of the Spouting Fish: Delhumide, the Mulhorandi imperial city, is razed by Red Wizards. The Second Mulhorandi Empire ends. Communication between Mulhorand and Khem comes to an end.
929, Year of Flashing Eyes: Several Chessentan cities form an alliance under the leadership of the warlord Tchazzar and secede from Unther.
934, Year of Fell Wizardry: Prince Ankh'Remun dies.
935, Year of the Rearing Lion: Start of the Curse of Ankh'Remun
939, Year of the Vengeful Halfling: Ankh'Remun city is abandoned and remaining people found Nes'ek.
976, Year of Slaying Spells: A Mulhorandi invasion of Thay is repelled.
1018, Year of the Dracorage: King Tchazzar of Chessenta dies in battle against sahuagin. His body is never found, so his people assume that he has ascended to godhood.
1020, Year of Smoldering Spells: First sahuagin spotted at Khems coasts. Thay develps much of its unique fire magic.
1098, Year of the Rose: A Thayan invasion of Mulhorand fails.
1050, Year of the Keening Gale: Lathandrites arrive in Nes'ek. Mulhorandi deities are slowly forgotten over the next century.
1183, Year of the Grisly Ghosts: Paladins of Osiris level the city of Sekras and clear Sebeks followers from the River of Swords.
1248, Year of the Cockatrice: Rehorusteb II becomes Pharaoh of Mulhorand.
1280, Year of the Manticore: Thay launches an invasion of Mulhorand and nearly overruns Sultim.
1296, Year of the Black Hound: Untherites establish a fortress on Khem to counter pirate raiding.
1317-1324: An epidemic of the Inner Sea takes a huge toll in Unther and Chessenta. It becomes known as the Plague of Dragons in the area due to its visible effect of causing the skin to flake and the madness brought onto its victims. Mulhorand is largely unaffected. The Untheric fortress and Nes'ek suffer badly, but smaller settlements are unaffected.
1320, Year of the Watching Cold: Akonhorus II becomes Pharaoh of Mulhorand.
1357, Year of the Prince: The Pharaoh of Mulhorand is assassinated by the cult of Step. Horustep III takes the throne of Mulhorand at age 11. Fire elementals ravage the coastal cities of the Old Empires, and Thayvian meddling is suspected.
1358, Year of Shadows: The Summer Storms War claims the lives of many sahuagin of the Alamber as well over thirty ships and 2,000 people of Mulhorand as the god-kings' forces clash with the sea devils. Assuran slays Ramman, bringing the Untheric pantheon to an end. Riots erupt throughout Unther, and the empire falls into chaos.
1369, Year of the Gauntlet: The island known as the Ship of the Gods explodes. Tidal waves swamp the Alaor and Bezantur, causing much destruction. Villages in the lowlands of Khem are swept away, but the flood also leaves unexpected things on the land. Mulhorand briefly seizes the Alaor.
1370, Year of the Tankard: Thay retakes the Alaor and rebuilds its shipyards and settlements with the aid of epic magic.
1371, Year of the Unstrung Harp: Mulhorand invades Unther, beginning the Third Mulhorand Empire. Untherite forces leave Khem and Mulhorandi traders start exploring the island.
